22/09/2009
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Fourteen people were slightly injured Monday (September 21st) in a train derailment near the town of Criova, in southern Romania.
Transport Minister Radu Berceanu visited the scene and said studs connecting the rails had been dismantled, a deliberate criminal act.
There were 300 passengers aboard the train, bound from Timisoara to Bucharest.
(Ziua, Nine o'clock - 22/09/09;
AFP - 21/09/09)
